sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M50051
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: IPTG Inducible Plasmid for the Expression of LsrR Repressor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This plasmid augments the natural expression of the LsrR repressor for the lsr operon. It is controlled through the induction of IPTG, allowing for close control of artificial expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anthony Agbay
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The genetic sequence of the LsrR gene was sourced through the UniProt database. Other parts were sourced through DNA 2.0 under the plasmid name pD444-CH.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We did not run into any major design considerations after analyzing our construct using Gene Designer.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PT5lac
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T5-lac promoter is a hybrid promoter made from the phage T5 early promoter and lac-operon. It contains three LacI binding sites and remains repressed in LacIq strains where LacI is expressed in high levels. It is inducible by IPTG, and recognizable by E.coli RNA polymerase. Compared to the T7 promoters, T5-lac promoter doesn't require the co-expression of phage polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Lundin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The most common DH5alpha and TOP10 used in assembly are not LacI-constitutive (LacIq) strains. Thus, any ORF placed downstream to this promoter will be massively transcribed. Therefore, it's recommended to employ low-copy number plasmids or even LacIq strains when adding genes to this promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M50028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: LsrR Repressor Protein for the Autoinducer-2 Pathway in E. coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the functional LsrR repressor protein for the autoinducer-2 pathway in E. coli. It represses the Lsr operon, preventing the intake of autoinducer-2 into the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anthony Agbay
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The genetic sequence was sourced from Uniprot under the name P76141 (LSRR_ECOLI).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: WE did not have to make any alterations of the original DNA sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: His-Stop
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is His-tag with stop codon. His-tag is used for detection of His-tagged proteins by anti-His antibodies. Cloned into pSB1AK3 vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Katja Kolar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Part was constructed by primer annealing.
